  summary: "Digital sovereignty refers to a nation\'s or individual\'s ability to control their digital destiny, including data, infrastructure, and digital services, without undue influence from foreign powers or large corporations. It emphasizes autonomy and self-determination in the digital realm. In AI policy, this concept is crucial for debates about data localization, national AI strategies, control over critical AI infrastructure, and ensuring that AI development aligns with national values and regulations rather than being dictated by external entities.",
