  summary: "Disaggregated data analysis involves breaking down data into smaller, more specific categories (e.g., by gender, race, age, or socioeconomic status) rather than looking at overall averages. This method helps reveal patterns, disparities, and inequalities that might be hidden in aggregated data. In AI policy, it\'s essential for identifying and mitigating bias in AI systems, ensuring fairness, and understanding how AI impacts different demographic groups. It allows policymakers to see if AI benefits or harms certain populations disproportionately.",
