  summary: "The dual-use technology concept refers to technologies that can serve both peaceful, beneficial civilian purposes and military or harmful applications. Examples include GPS, which aids navigation but also guides missiles, or drones used for delivery and surveillance. In AI policy, this concept is fundamental for understanding the inherent challenges in regulating AI, as many AI advancements (e.g., computer vision, natural language processing) have both positive societal uses and potential for misuse in surveillance, warfare, or manipulation.",
