  summary: "This theory explains how new ideas, technologies, and practices spread through a social system over time, identifying different adopter categories like innovators and early adopters. In AI policy, it helps understand how AI technologies are adopted across industries and society, informing strategies for promoting beneficial AI, managing resistance to change, and designing policies that facilitate responsible AI integration.",
