  label: "Existential Risk Theory (Societal Collapse Scenarios)",
  summary: "This aspect of existential risk theory focuses on scenarios where AI doesn\'t necessarily cause human extinction but leads to the irreversible breakdown of complex human societies. In AI policy, it prompts consideration of how AI could exacerbate existing societal vulnerabilities, disrupt critical infrastructure, or undermine democratic institutions, requiring policies that build resilience, prevent widespread instability, and protect fundamental societal functions.",
