  summary: "Future of work studies is an interdisciplinary field that examines how technological, economic, and social changes, particularly automation and AI, will reshape employment, job skills, and the nature of work itself. It investigates potential job displacement, the creation of new jobs, and the evolving demands on the workforce. In AI policy, this field directly informs policies on education, workforce retraining, social safety nets, and labor market regulations to prepare for and adapt to AI\'s impact on jobs and economic inequality.",
