  summary: "Human-centered design is a design philosophy and process that focuses on understanding the needs, behaviors, and motivations of the people for whom a product or service is being designed. It emphasizes empathy, iterative development, and user feedback to create solutions that are highly usable and desirable. In AI policy, this provides a foundational approach for developing AI systems that are user-friendly, ethical, and effective, with policy encouraging or mandating its application to ensure AI serves human needs and values.",
