  summary: "IT project management literature comprises the body of knowledge, methodologies, and best practices for planning, executing, and closing information technology projects. It covers topics like scope management, risk assessment, resource allocation, and stakeholder communication. In AI policy, this literature is relevant for understanding the practical challenges and strategies involved in developing, deploying, and maintaining AI systems within organizations, including managing the unique risks and complexities associated with AI projects.",
