  summary: "This field examines how societies perceive, define, and respond to risks, often highlighting that risk is not just an objective fact but also a social construct influenced by culture, values, and power. It looks at who benefits and who suffers from different risk assessments. In AI policy, it helps understand public fears about AI, how different groups assess AI\'s dangers (e.g., job loss, privacy invasion, autonomous weapons), and how these perceptions influence policy decisions and public acceptance of AI technologies.",
