  summary: "Unintended consequences in complex systems refer to the unexpected and often undesirable outcomes that arise from actions or interventions within systems with many interacting parts, where cause and effect are not always clear. In AI policy, this highlights the need to anticipate and mitigate unforeseen negative impacts of deploying AI, such as widespread job displacement, algorithmic bias leading to societal harm, or the emergence of new vulnerabilities in interconnected AI systems.",
